Test Your Omni-Channel Implementation

Now that you've got Omni-Channel set up, test your implementation to make sure it's working correctly.

To test your implementation, route a work item to yourself. Log in as a user who's enabled to use Omni-Channel and change your status so that you can receive incoming work items.

Navigate to the record corresponding to the service channel you've set for your current presence status. Select the checkbox next to the record or open it if using Lightning Experience. Click Change Owner, select Queue, enter the name of the queue associated with your routing configuration, and click Submit.

You'll see an incoming request notification in Omni-Channel within a few seconds.
title: Testing Omni-Channel Implementation
